5:
They want to stop working with us
too? How many companies is that,
now?
7:
Forty companies cited harassment
as a reason for leaving. Twenty were
threatened, and fifty others left
without giving a reason!
9:
...We also received that same
message again: "CI is welcome to
apply to become a subsidiary of
AltMeme at any time."
12:
Those guys never quit, do they?
We've turned them down a
thousand times...
15:
All right. I guess the partnership is
dissolved, then. I'll have to find us
another partner, so you can take the
rest of the day off.
19:
...Are you really okay with letting it
fall apart like that?
22:
Of course. We have to take any
opportunities we can, but
sometimes we just have to cut our
losses.
24:
...It doesn't take the sting away
though. I still feel it every time.
28:
...Um, Quinvere? Why don't you take
the day off, too?
31:
You've been dealing with
troublemakers nonstop. I'm sure
your employees are worried about
you...
42:
How about a date then, Alk? I
wouldn't mind getting a little R & R
with a good-looking guy.
58:
Was that... a massage? My body
feels so light... TOO light, actually!
63:
Nothing beats a yokai massage. I
made a contract with a certain
somebody to open a business here.
67:
And it seems you have found great
success. It took some time, but
eventually the villagers understood
how such a business could benefit
them.
69:
However. Before that, this person
entered a dangerous area without
permission, released yokai and very
nearly started a war.
78:
Hehe! Conflict provides some of the
best opportunities, don't you think?
This is only the beginning of a long
and eventful relationship with the
Diviners' Commission!
82:
Indeed. A great many things are
sure to come as a result of our new
relationship. All of them positive, yes.
I cannot wait.
86:
You're actually mad, huh? That's...
rare...
92:
Now then! It's time to get a little
exercise!
106:
How'd you get the airship here?!
Why skydiving?! And why the heck is
Regis with us?!
111:
You mentioned me as though I were
merely an afterthought.
115:
I got permission to build a base
here. I think I'll be making some
huge investments into the Updaters
and Defaulters!
122:
Heh-heh! It seemed like it would be
more fun to be adversaries. Hope
you're ready for me, Regis!
130: You don't look so good, Regis!
135: Enough chitchat, let's get to jumping!
140:
W-wait a second! I'm not ready for
something like th
153:
...This... This is delicious.
No, "delicious" doesn't do this flavor
justice!
157:
This is the finest full-course meal
money can buy in Palpebra. We've
got the whole restaurant to
ourselves today, so let's just drop all
the etiquette and dig in!
162:
I probably don't need to say this,
but...
164:
I don't know if much of this counts
as "R & R." You've been pulling us
around everywhere nonstop.
168:
Oh. Were you not enjoying
yourselves?
173: No, we're having lots of fun.
177:
I'm just... a little overwhelmed with
the scope of your activities. I didn't
expect so many people to be
involved.
181:
Heh-heh, I'm just on a roll, you
know? With access to all these
amazing worlds, I wanted to make
the most of it.
183:
But it's still not enough. I've got so
many things I need to change in my
own world...
185:
...And I guess rejection is just
something I'll always have to put up
with in this kind of job.
195:
I sure do! You can patch things up
with a friend after a fight, but going
your separate ways with somebody
usually marks the end.
198:
Even still, I can't stop trying to move
forward. You never know when your
next big high in life is just around the
corner.
200:
I mean, that outlook eventually led
me to you guys, didn't it?
205:
...Hey, is it okay if we pick the last
destination for tonight?
213:
Took away my breath for a moment,
even. I'm reminded that there's so
much out there I haven't seen yet!
222:
Yeah. I might not be wired the same
way as you, but...
224:
I wouldn't mind doing more stuff
together. Heck, even the skydiving
was pretty fun.
229: You two are simply the best!
231:
So cute, yet so cool. So soft, but so
intense... I can't stop loving you guys!
241:
Oh dear, did I come on a little too
strong?
244:
Alk, Stella... Thank you. I think that
was some of the best R & R I've ever
had.
248:
Hey! I treated you guys earlier, so I
was hoping you might return the
favor with your cooking, Alk!
251:
My cooking? I don't think my skills
will be able to compare with what
we had at the restaurant...
254: I do LOVE the food there, but...
258:
Today, nothing would hit the spot
better than a meal prepared by
Chef Alk himself! What do you say?
262:
Well, if you put it like that...
Please wait here for a little bit.
267:
Hehe! We'll be eating well tonight,
Stella!
